      <title>Iraqi Refugees Return From Syria to Undocumented Lives</title>
      <category domain="https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/crises-conflicts/">Crises &amp; Conflicts</category>
      <pubDate>Mon, 13 Mar 2017 05:01:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Shelly Kittleson</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/refugees/articles/2017/03/13/iraqi-refugees-return-from-syria-to-undocumented-lives</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/refugees/articles/2017/03/13/iraqi-refugees-return-from-syria-to-undocumented-lives</guid>
      <description>Some Iraqis who fled across the Syrian border ahead of the Mosul offensive are now returning to Iraq. Many say their official IDs were confiscated in Syria, leaving them trapped in Iraqi displacement camps and unable to prove their identities.</description>
